}}

[[L'Oreal]] Paris named Lopez their new Global Ambassador and the face of their brands, including EverPure hair care, Preference hair color and Youth Code skin care. Her EverSleek hair care ads made their debut in early 2011, to coincide with the release of ''Love?'' and her debut as a judge on ''American Idol''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realstylenetwork.com/blogs/beauty/2010/12/jennifer-lopez-named-loreal-paris-global-ambassador |title=Jennifer Lopez Named L'Oreal Paris Global Ambassador |publisher=Real Style Network |date=December 3, 2010 |accessdate=August 8, 2012}}</ref> To further promote her comeback, in February, [[Gillette Mach3|Venus]] chose Lopez as their new Global Ambassador.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realstylenetwork.com/blogs/beauty/2011/02/jennifer-lopez-is-the-new-venus-global-ambassador |title=Jennifer Lopez Is The New Venus Global Ambassador |publisher=Real Style Network |date=February 3, 2011 |accessdate=August 8, 2012}}</ref> Lopez's comeback single "[[On the Floor]]" was released later that same month. The song topped the charts across the globe, becoming one of the most successful singles of the year.<ref name="Digital report 2012">{{cite web|title=IFPI digital music report 2012&nbsp;– key facts and figures |url=http://ifpi.com/content/library/DMR2012_key_facts_and_figures.pdf|publisher=[[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]]|accessdate=January 23, 2012}}</ref> The song also became her highest charting single commercially as a lead artist, as well as her most successful airplay hit on [[contemporary hit radio]], since "Jenny from the Block".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/471634/beastie-boys-score-no-2-debut-on-billboard-200-adele-holds-at-no-1 |title=Beastie Boys Score No. 2 Debut on Billboard 200, Adele Holds at No. 1 |work=Billboard |last=Caulfield |first=Keith |date=May 11, 2011 |accessdate=May 29, 2011}}</ref> ''Love?'', which was released in May, was a moderate commercial success, and was viewed as a humble comeback from Lopez, as many had considered her recording career over.<ref name=lovereview>{{cite web|last=Copsey|first=Robert|title=Jennifer Lopez: 'Love?'|url=http://www.digitalspy.com.au/music/albumreviews/a317729/jennifer-lopez-love.html|publisher=Digital Spy |accessdate=January 29, 2012|date=May 4, 2011}}</ref> Lopez launched her next fragrance Love and Light in July, exclusively on HSN. 51,000 bottles of the fragrance were sold at its premiere, becoming Lopez's most successful fragrance launch to date, making over $2.9 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.instyle.com/2011/07/07/jennifer-lopez-hsn-love-and-light-sales |title=Jennifer Lopez HSN&nbsp;– Love & Light |work=InStyle |date=July 7, 2011 |accessdate=August 8, 2012}}</ref> In September, Lopez launched the [[Jennifer Lopez Collection]], a clothing and accessories line for [[Kohl's]] with [[Tommy Hilfiger]].<ref name="goahead">{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez&nbsp;– Jennifer Lopez's Fashion Line To Go Ahead|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/jennifer-lopezs-fashion-line-to-go-ahead_1233187|publisher=Contactmusic News |accessdate=February 5, 2012|date=July 19, 2011}}</ref> In addition to the clothing line, she also launched the Jennifer Lopez Home Collection, featuring bedding, towels and luggage.<ref name="Lopez Previews Her Kohl's Collection">{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez Previews Her Kohl's Collection|url=http://stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com/2011/08/12/jennifer-lopez-for-kohls|publisher=Style News|accessdate=January 31, 2012|date=August 12, 2011}}</ref> Later that same month [[Fiat]], an Italian automobile manufacturer, enlisted Lopez to promote their products, including the [[Fiat 500 (2007)|2012 Fiat 500 Cabrio]]. Olivier Francois, the [[Chrysler]] chief marketing officer, stated that she "fits perfectly with the brand".<ref>{{cite web|last=Lienert |first=Anita |url=http://www.insideline.com/fiat/500/2012/fiat-and-jennifer-lopez-hook-up.html |title=Fiat and Jennifer Lopez Hook Up |publisher=[[Insideline]] |date=September 13, 2011 |accessdate=August 8, 2012}}</ref>

In January 2012, Lopez returned as a judge on the [[American Idol (season 11)|eleventh season]] of ''American Idol'', earning a reported $20 million.<ref name="Forbes2">{{cite news|author=Hannah Elliott |url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/hannahelliott/2012/05/16/the-real-american-idol-how-j-lo-got-her-mojo-back/ |title=The Real American Idol: How J.Lo Got Her Mojo Back |work=[[Forbes]] |date=April 18, 2012 |accessdate=May 24, 2012}}</ref> Later that same month, a new talent show, ''[[Q'Viva! The Chosen|¡Q'Viva! The Chosen]]'', created by [[Simon Fuller]] premiered on [[Univision]] and was a hit for the channel.<ref>{{cite news|last=Sheridan|first=Emily|title='Sometimes you don't agree and I say be quiet': Jennifer Lopez admits it can be difficult working with estranged husband Marc Anthony|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2094297/Jennifer-Lopez-admits-difficult-working-estranged-husband-Marc-Anthony.html|work=[[Daily Mail]] |accessdate=February 12, 2012|date=January 31, 2012|location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jennifer-lopez-marc-anthonys-qviva-250584 | work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] | title=Jennifer Lopez and Marc Anthony's 'Q'Viva: The Chosen': First Broadcast Partners Announced | date=October 19, 2011}}</ref> It followed Lopez, Anthony and director-choeographer [[Jamie King]] as they travelled across 21 countries in Latin America to find new talent for a [[Las Vegas]] show. On May 18, Lopez returned to the big screen starring alongside an [[ensemble cast]] consisting of [[Cameron Diaz]], [[Elizabeth Banks]], [[Matthew Morrison]] and [[Dennis Quaid]] in the film ''[[What to Expect When You're Expecting (film)|What to Expect When You're Expecting]]''.<ref name="Lopez">{{cite news|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2011/06/24/jennifer-lopez-what-to-expect-when-youre-expecting|title=Jennifer Lopez signs on for 'What to Expect When You're Expecting'|last=Labrecque|first=Jeff|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=June 24, 2011|accessdate=July 23, 2011<!--archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/60O53uOVo |archivedate=July 23, 2011 -->}}</ref> Based on the [[What to Expect When You're Expecting|novel of the same name]], Lopez plays Holly, a woman who adopts a baby from abroad with her husband after difficulty conceiving. In late May, Lopez released her fragrance Glowing by JLo, which she described as an "evolution" of Glow by JLo.<ref name="Huffington">{{cite news|first=Michelle |last=Manetti |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/02/10/glowing-jennifer-lopez-launching-new-fragrance_n_1268972.html |title=Jennifer Lopez Launches 'Glowing' Perfume With Naked Ad, Light-Up Bottle (Photos) |work=[[The Huffington Post]] |accessdate=March 3, 2012 |date=February 10, 2012}}</ref>

[[File:Jennifer Lopez 2, 2012.jpg|thumb|left|180px|Lopez performing during her [[Dance Again World Tour]], June 2012.]]

Lopez launched the [[Dance Again World Tour]], her first headlining concert tour, on June 14.<ref name="My Diary May 3">{{cite web |url=http://jenniferlopez.com/blog/post/my-diary|title=My Diary |date=May 3, 2012 |publisher=Jennifer Lopez Website |accessdate=May 13, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.freezepage.com/1336988633AFEXHXNLRN |archivedate=May 13, 2012}}</ref> It was a lucrative, grossing over $1 million per show.<ref name="Forbes 2013" /> On July 12, Lopez launched [[Teeology]], a luxury [[T-shirt]] [[e-commerce]].<ref>{{cite news |author=Andrea Huspeni |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/jennifer-lopez-to-launch-teeology-2012-7 |title=Jennifer Lopez to Launch Teeology |publisher=Business Insider, Inc. |date=July 12, 2012 |accessdate=August 5, 2012}}</ref> Lopez voiced Shira, a saber tooth tiger, in the animated film, ''[[Ice Age: Continental Drift]]'', the fourth film in the ''[[Ice Age (franchise)|Ice Age]]'' franchise.<ref name="Rovi Ice Age 4">{{cite web|first=Jeremy |last=Wheeler |url=http://www.allrovi.com/movies/movie/ice-age-continental-drift-3d-v516738 |title=Ice Age: Continental Drift 3D&nbsp;– Cast, Reviews, Summary, and Awards |publisher=AllRovi |accessdate=October 30, 2011}}</ref> The film  became Lopez's highest opening weekend figure.<ref>{{cite news|agency=Associated Press|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2174019/Ice-Age-4-Continental-Drift-movie-tops-box-office-46m-opening-weekend.html|title=Ice Age movie tops box office with $46 million opening weekend...but Batman is lurking to snatch the title|date=July 15, 2012|work=[[Daily Mail]] |accessdate=July 24, 2012}}</ref>

Lopez's first greatest hits album, ''[[Dance Again... the Hits]]'', was released on July 24, 2012 in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a388349/jennifer-lopez-to-release-dance-again-the-hits-next-month.html |title=Jennifer Lopez to release 'Dance Again: The Hits' next month? |publisher=Digital Spy |date=June 19, 2012 |accessdate=July 10, 2012}}</ref> It was released by Epic Records, as Lopez owed them one final album to end her contract, despite previously announcing that she had fulfilled her contract with the label.<ref name="radio1">{{cite web|url=http://925maxima.radio.com/2012/05/28/jennifer-lopez-interview-new-single-goin-in |title=Jennifer Lopez Talks About Her New Single "Goin' In" |publisher=925maxima Radio|date=May 28, 2012 |accessdate=June 23, 2012}}</ref> Lopez, who was going through a divorce with Anthony and the "breakup of a family", felt as if the album's sole single, "[[Dance Again]]", had come to her at the "perfect moment".<ref name="ryaninterview">{{cite web|first=Michael |last=Murray |url=http://ryanseacrest.com/2012/03/30/jennifer-lopez-talks-dance-again-her-upcoming-album-audio/ |title=Jennifer Lopez Talks 'Dance Again' & Her Upcoming 'Greatest Hits' Album |publisher=Ryan Seacrest Productions |date=March 30, 2012 |accessdate=March 31, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120402195736/http://ryanseacrest.com/2012/03/30/jennifer-lopez-talks-dance-again-her-upcoming-album-audio/ |archivedate=April 2, 2012 }}</ref><ref name="AOL2">{{cite web|last=Gayles|first=Contessa|title=Jennifer Lopez, Divorce: Real Reason Singer Went on World Tour?|url=http://blog.music.aol.com/2012/12/06/jennifer-lopez-divorce-tour/|publisher=[[AOL|AOL Music Blog]]|accessdate=December 7, 2012|date=December 6, 2012}}</ref> "Dance Again" and "[[Goin' In]]", a single from the soundtrack of the dance film ''[[Step Up Revolution]]'', both reached the top of the ''Billboard'' Hot Dance Club Songs, giving Lopez her twelfth and thirteenth number one on that chart, respectively. Additionally, "Goin' In" became her tenth consecutive number one on the chart, tying [[Katy Perry]] for having the most consecutive numbers ones on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/chartbeat/480578/chart-highlights-gotye-extends-multi-format-chart-success |title=Latest Music News, Band, Artist, Musician & Music Video News |work=Billboard |date=August 6, 2012 |accessdate=August 8, 2012}}</ref> [[nuvoTV]] announced in September its premier partnership with Lopez, that will see her work on the creative side of the network, managing marketing and program production with her production company, [[Nuyorican Productions]], as well as periodically appearing in network programming.<ref name="Jennifer Lopez Partnering With NuvoTV">{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/09/13/jennifer-lopez-nuvotv_n_1880503.html |title=Jennifer Lopez Partnering With NuvoTV, Takes Equity Stake In Cable Network |work=The Huffington Post|date=September 13, 2012 |accessdate=September 16, 2012 |first=Samreen |last=Hooda}}</ref><ref name="Jennifer Lopez to Take Minority Stake in Cable's Nuvo TV">{{cite news |last=Steinberg |first=Brian |url=http://adage.com/article/media/jennifer-lopez-minority-stake-cable-s-nuvo-tv/237139 |title=Jennifer Lopez to Take Minority Stake in Cable's Nuvo TV |work=[[Advertising Age]] |date=September 12, 2012 |accessdate=September 16, 2012}}</ref> In December, Lopez held a charity drive that would affect her three favorite charities: the [[Gloria Wise Boys and Girls Club]], the Children's Hospital of Los Angeles as well as the [[American Red Cross]], which would mainly benefit victims of [[Hurricane Sandy]], which devastated parts of her home town, New York City.<ref name="HSp">{{cite web|last=Moody|first=Nekesa|title=Jennifer Lopez on Holiday Charity Drive and Jenni Rivera: 'It's a Wake-Up Call'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin-notas/1481338/jennifer-lopez-on-holiday-charity-drive-and-jenni-rivera-its-a|work=Billboard |accessdate=January 3, 2013|date=December 17, 2012}}</ref>

===2013–15: Television ventures and ''A.K.A.'' ===

In January 2013, Lopez starred alongside [[Jason Statham]] in the crime thriller ''[[Parker (2013 film)|Parker]]'', in which she played Leslie. Her performance earned positive reviews, with ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'' commending the role for giving Lopez "an opportunity to be dramatic, romantic, funny, depressed, euphoric and violent. The audience stays with her all the way".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/sns-201301251600--tms--lizsmittr--x-a20130128-20130128,0,6035496.story |title=Hackford's 'Parker' packs a big punch |newspaper=Chicago Tribune |date=January 28, 2013 |accessdate=December 5, 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130729082325/http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/sns-201301251600--tms--lizsmittr--x-a20130128-20130128,0,6035496.story |archivedate=2013-07-29}}</ref> It under-performed at the box office, however.<ref>{{cite web|title=Parker-Box Office Data|url=http://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Parker|publisher=The Numbers|accessdate=May 6, 2013}}</ref> The following month, she gained widespread notoriety for wearing a daring black dress at the [[2013 Grammy Awards|Grammy Awards]], which revealed her entire right leg; despite a conservative dress code which had been issued to celebrities in attendance.<ref>{{cite news|author=Christie D'Zurilla |url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/gossip/la-et-mg-jennifer-lopez-vs-angelina-jolie-leg-grammys-20130210,0,5894431.story |title=Jennifer Lopez vs. Angelina Jolie: Which leg do you love? |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=February 11, 2013 |accessdate=April 19, 2013}}</ref> In May, Lopez was announced as the [[chief creative officer]] of nuvoTV. In addition, she founded the mobile phone retail brand [[Viva Móvil]], which is catered specifically for Latinos.<ref>{{cite web|last=Cheng |first=Roger |url=http://reviews.cnet.com/8301-12261_7-57585831-10356022/jennifer-lopez-dishes-on-new-viva-movil-shopping-q-a |title=Jennifer Lopez dishes on new Viva Movil shopping (Q&A) |publisher=Cnet Reviews|date=May 23, 2013 |accessdate=May 24, 2013}}</ref> In these media ventures, Lopez hoped to empower the Latin community, stating that: "We're realizing our power. We're realizing that we matter here. You know, we're not just, you know, the guys working behind the scenes in the kitchens and as a plumber."<ref name="Latino1">{{cite news|url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2013/06/13/jennifer-lopez-wants-latinos-to-realizing-our-power/ |title=Jennifer Lopez Wants Latinos To Realize Their Power |publisher=Fox News Latino|date=June 13, 2013 |accessdate=June 18, 2013}}</ref> She lobbied for more Hispanic diversity on television;<ref>{{cite news|author=Debbie Emery |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2340639/Jennifer-Lopez-makes-strong-political-stance-power-suit-spiked-stilettos-takes-Washington-DC.html?ito=feeds-newsxml |title=Jennifer Lopez makes a strong political stance in a power suit and spiked stilettos when she takes on Washington DC |date=June 14, 2013 |newspaper=Daily Mail |accessdate=June 18, 2013}}</ref> "There's a big revolution going on, it's like a media and cultural revolution of Latinos here in the United States. We're realizing our power. We're realizing that we matter here."<ref name="Latino1" />

[[File:The opening ceremony of the FIFA World Cup 2014 13 (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|200px|Lopez performing during the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] opening ceremony in [[Brazil]]]]

Inspired by her gay aunt who had died, Lopez signed on as executive producer of the television series ''[[The Fosters (2013 TV series)|The Fosters]]'', which is about a same-sex couple raising a family.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/04/24/jennifer-lopez-declares-the-fosters_n_3149200.html |title=Jennifer Lopez's Lesbian Aunt: Star Says 'The Fosters' TV Show Inspired By Late Relative |work=The Huffington Post  |date=April 24, 2013 |accessdate=May 31, 2013}}</ref> The show premiered on [[ABC Family]] on June 3, 2013, and has since been a ratings success for the network.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/06/11/monday-cable-ratings-love-hip-hop-wins-night-wwe-raw-teen-wolf-major-crimes-switched-at-birth-longmire-more/186745/|title=Monday Cable Ratings: 'Love & Hip Hop' Wins Night, 'WWE Raw', 'Teen Wolf’, 'Major Crimes', 'Switched at Birth', 'Longmire' & More&nbsp;– Ratings |last=Bibel|first=Sara |work=The Numbers |date=June 11, 2013}}</ref> She was awarded the Ally for Equality award presented by the [[Human Rights Campaign]].<ref>{{cite web|title=HRC to Honor Jennifer Lopez with Ally for Equality Award at 2013 National Dinner|url=http://www.hrc.org/blog/entry/hrc-to-honor-jennifer-lopez-with-ally-for-equality-award-at-2013-national-d|work=HRC Blog|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|accessdate=September 25, 2013|date=September 20, 2013}}</ref> Later that June, Lopez performed at the birthday of [[Turkmenistan]] President [[Gurbanguly Berdymukhamedov]].<ref name="Turkmenistan, Washington Post" /> Doing so, she garnered widespread backlash for performing for the leader of a "repressive, authoritarian regime".<ref>{{cite web|title=J. Lo comes under attack after singing for leader of Turkmenistan|url=http://twitchy.com/2013/06/30/j-lo-comes-under-attack-after-singing-for-leader-of-turkmenistan/?utm_source=twitterfeed&utm_medium=twitter|publisher=Twitchy.com|accessdate=June 30, 2013|date=June 30, 2013}}</ref> Her publicist released an apology.<ref name="Turkmenistan, Washington Post">{{cite news|title=Jennifer Lopez apologizes for Turkmenistan performance|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/reliable-source/wp/2013/06/30/jennifer-lopez-sings-for-dictator-paula-deen-loses-cookbook/|work=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=July 1, 2013|date=June 30, 2013}}</ref> Lopez returned as judge on ''American Idol'' for its [[American Idol (season 13)|thirteenth season]] for a reported salary of $17.5 million.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lopez to earn USD 17.5 million for American Idol return|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/lopez-to-earn-usd-17-5-million-for-american-idol-return-113090100045_1.html|work=Business Standard |accessdate=September 24, 2013|date=September 1, 2013}}</ref> She was ranked as the fifth highest-paid woman in music for 2013, having earned $45 million.<ref name="Forbes 2013">{{cite news |title=No. 5: Jennifer Lopez ($45 million)|url=http://www.forbes.com/pictures/eeel45eglhi/no-5-jennifer-lopez-45-million/|work=Forbes |accessdate=February 8, 2015}}</ref> After the conclusion of her Dance Again World Tour, Lopez began recording her eighth studio album, ''[[A.K.A. (album)|A.K.A.]]'', inspired by her travels.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lopez didn't expect new album so soon|url=http://au.news.yahoo.com/entertainment/a/-/entertainment/17557067/lopez-didnt-expect-new-album-so-soon/|publisher=Yahoo! News |accessdate=June 13, 2013|date=June 11, 2013}}{{dead link|date=November 2015}}</ref> It was released in June 2014 through [[Capitol Records]], experiencing lackluster sales.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lipshutz|first1=Jason|title=Jennifer Lopez's 'A.K.A.' Debut: An Icon Reaches a Crossroads|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6141007/jennifer-lopez-aka-debut-sales-pop-column|website=Billboard |accessdate=January 24, 2015|date=June 30, 2014}}</ref> The album produced three singles: "[[I Luh Ya Papi]]", which features [[French Montana]], "[[First Love (Jennifer Lopez song)|First Love]]", and "[[Booty (song)|Booty]]", featuring Pitbull or rapper [[Iggy Azalea]]. "Booty" reached the top twenty in the United States and was certified platinum.<ref name=hot100>{{cite news|last1=Trust|first1=Gary|title=Meghan Trainor No. 1 On Hot 100, Jeremih Hits Top 10, Jennifer Lopez Debuts|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6259336/hot-100-meghan-trainor-jeremih-jennifer-lopez|accessdate=September 25, 2014|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=September 24, 2014}}</ref> In April, the official song for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] performed by [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]], Lopez and Brazilian recording artist [[Claudia Leitte]], "[[We Are One (Ole Ola)]]", was released. She was ranked as the sixth highest-paid woman in music for the year, earning $37 million.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez ($37 million)|url=http://www.forbes.com/pictures/eeel45emikk/6-jennifer-lopez-37-million/|website=Forbes |accessdate=January 25, 2015}}</ref> In November 2014, Lopez partnered with Endless Jewelry, designing a range of new jewelry products.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cheng|first1=Andrea|title=Here's Your First Look at Jennifer Lopez's New Jewelry Designs|url=http://www.instyle.com/news/heres-your-first-look-jennifer-lopezs-new-jewelry-designs|website=InStyle |accessdate=September 21, 2015|date=January 15, 2015}}</ref>

January 2015 saw the release of ''[[The Boy Next Door (film)|The Boy Next Door]]'', an erotic thriller that Lopez both co-produced and starred in as a high school teacher who becomes involved with a student, which eventually leads to his dangerous obsession with her.<ref name="HuffPost Latino">{{cite news |last1=Moreno|first1=Carolina|title=Jennifer Lopez On Why Her New Movie Is 'Breaking Down' Stereotypes|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/12/23/jennifer-lopez-ryan-guzman_n_6373936.html|publisher=The Huffington Post|accessdate=December 27, 2014|date=December 23, 2014}}</ref> The film received negative reviews from critics.<ref>{{cite news|title='Strange Magic,' 'Mortdecai,' 'The Boy Next Door': Review Revue|url=http://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2015/01/23/strange-magic-mortdecai-the-boy-next-door-review-revue/|accessdate=January 24, 2015|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |date=January 23, 2015}}</ref> Despite this, it became her most successful opening at the box office for a live action film since ''Monster-in-Law'',<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mendelson|first1=Scott|title=Friday Box Office: Johnny Depp's 'Mortdecai' Flops, Jennifer Lopez's 'Boy Next Door' Scores|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2015/01/24/friday-box-office-johnny-depps-mortdecai-flops-jennifer-lopezs-boy-next-door-scores/|website=Forbes |accessdate=January 26, 2015|date=January 24, 2015}}</ref> and ultimately grossed over $50 million at the global box office, against a production budget of $4 million.<ref name="Box Office Mojo">{{cite web|title=The Boy Next Door (2015)|url=http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=boynextdoor.htm|website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=March 10, 2015}}</ref> The following month, she unveiled her next fragrance, JLuxe.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Parker|first1=Heidi|title=Now she's just showing off! Jennifer Lopez, 45, reveals her impressive cleavage yet again for sexy new JLuxe perfume ad|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2941621/Jennifer-Lopez-45-reveals-impressive-cleavage-sexy-new-JLuxe-perfume-ad.html|accessdate=February 8, 2015|work=[[Daily Mail]] |date=February 6, 2015}}</ref> Lopez had a voice role in the animated feature ''[[Home (2015 comedy film)|Home]]'', alongside [[Steve Martin]], [[Jim Parsons]], and [[Rihanna]], and released in March 2015.<ref name="Martin & Lopez">{{cite web|last=Dickey|first=Josh|title=Jennifer Lopez, Steve Martin Board DreamWorks Animation's 'Home' (Exclusive)|url=http://www.thewrap.com/steve-martin-jennifer-lopez-board-dreamworks-animations-home-exclusive/|publisher=The Wrap News Inc|accessdate=October 4, 2013|date=October 3, 2013}}</ref> She contributed the single "[[Feel the Light]]" to the film's official soundtrack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/jennifer-lopez/news/premiere-watch-jennifer-lopezs-cute-feel-the-light-video|title=Exclusive! Watch Jennifer Lopez's Cute 'Feel The Light' Video|work=''[[MTV (UK and Ireland)|MTV UK]]''|last=Pell|first=Michael|date=February 24, 2015|accessdate=February 26, 2015}}</ref> Lopez also starred in the independent drama film ''[[Lila & Eve]]'', alongside [[Viola Davis]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Seidman|first=Robert|title=Viola Davis & Jennifer Lopez To Star In Indie Film 'Lila and Eve' Produced By Lifetime Films & A+E Studios|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/01/27/viola-davis-jennifer-lopez-to-star-in-indie-film-lila-and-eve-produced-by-lifetime-films-ae-studios/232388/|work=[[Zap2it]] |accessdate=March 11, 2014|date=January 27, 2014}}</ref> She was a featured speaker during the general session at VentureScape 2015 to discuss women entrepreneurship and diversity in [[San Francisco]] during May 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://us10.campaign-archive2.com/?u=d968159ab2731f4d34a857d11&id=39eea4d051&e=b5120008a6|title=Program Update: Jennifer Lopez to Discuss Women Entrepreneurship and Diversity during Fireside Chat at VentureScape 2015|date=|work=campaign-archive2.com|accessdate=November 10, 2015}}</ref> That September, Lopez was announced as the first Global Advocate for Girls and Women at the [[United Nations Foundation]].<ref>{{cite news |title=United Nations Foundation Announces Jennifer Lopez as Global Advocate for Girls and Women|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2015/9/prweb12978264.htm|website=''PRWeb'' |accessdate=September 23, 2015|date=September 24, 2015}}</ref> With annual earnings of $28.5 million, she was ranked as the seventh highest-paid woman in music for 2015.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Falcone|first1=Dana Rose|title=Katy Perry beats out Taylor Swift to become 2015's highest-paid woman in music|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/11/05/katy-perry-highest-paid-woman-music-2015|website=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=March 26, 2016}}</ref>

===2016: ''Shades of Blue'' and residency show ===

[[File:JLoVegas All I Have.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Lopez performing during her [[Jennifer Lopez: All I Have|All I Have]] residency in Las Vegas, 2016.]]

Lopez stars as Detective Harlee Santos in [[NBC]]'s crime drama series ''[[Shades of Blue (TV series)|Shades of Blue]]'' (also serving as an executive producer), a single mother and police detective who goes undercover for the FBI to investigate her own squad. [[Ryan Seacrest]] produces the series.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://variety.com/2014/tv/news/nbc-orders-cop-drama-starring-jennifer-lopez-to-series-1201116116/ |title=NBC Orders Cop Drama Starring Jennifer Lopez to Series |work=Variety |date=February 21, 2014 |accessdate=July 20, 2014}}</ref> It premiered on January 7, 2016, giving the network its most-watched Thursday debut in seven years with 8.6 million viewers.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Maglio|first1=Tony|title=Ratings: J Lo's 'Shades of Blue' Is Most-Watched NBC Thursday Debut in 7 Years|url=http://www.thewrap.com/jennifer-lopez-shades-of-blue-ray-liotta-american-idol-nbc-tv-ratings-fox/|publisher=TheWrap|accessdate=January 8, 2016}}</ref> It was picked up for a second season the following month.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/jennifer-lopezs-shades-blue-renewed-862516|title=Jennifer Lopez's 'Shades of Blue' Renewed at NBC|last=O'Connell|first=Michael|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=February 5, 2016|accessdate=February 5, 2016}}</ref> Her performance received positive reviews.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Paskin|first1=Willa|title=Shades of Blue|publisher=Slate|date=January 6, 2016|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/arts/television/2016/01/shades_of_blue_on_nbc_starring_jennifer_lopez_reviewed.html|accessdate=January 7, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Tucker|first1=Ken|title='Shades of Blue' Review: J. Lo Gets Low-Down|url=https://www.yahoo.com/tv/shades-of-blue-review-jennifer-lopez-140321526.html|publisher=Yahoo!|accessdate=January 7, 2016|date=January 7, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Rotten Tomatoes TV|shades-of-blue/s01}}</ref> Lopez reprised her voice role as Shira in the animated film ''[[Ice Age: Collision Course]]'', which was released in July 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ice Age: Collision Course|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=iceage5.htm|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|publisher=[[Amazon.com]]|accessdate=June 30, 2016}}</ref> She is set to star in the comedy film ''Mothers I'd Like To...'', for which she will also serve as a producer through her production company.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Fleming, Jr.|first1=Mike|title=Jennifer Lopez Object Of 'Mothers I'd Like To...': Universal Buys Comedy Pitch|url=http://deadline.com/2015/04/jennifer-lopez-mothers-i-would-like-to-universal-pictures-1201409904/|website=''[[Deadline.com]]''|accessdate=August 12, 2015|date=April 14, 2015}}</ref> Lopez will star as drug lord [[Griselda Blanco]] in a television film for [[HBO]], which will focus on the "rise and fall" of Blanco. She will once more serve as an executive producer for the film, which is currently in development.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Goldberg|first1=Lesley|title=Jennifer Lopez to Play Drug Lord Griselda Blanco in HBO TV Movie|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/jennifer-lopez-play-drug-lord-918749|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=August 11, 2016|date=August 10, 2016}}</ref>

Lopez has revealed plans to release a Christmas album followed by a second Spanish-language album.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nagi|first1=Ariel|title=J.Lo Plans to Make Another Spanish Album Next Year|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/news/a26520/jlo-spanish-album/|website=[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]] |accessdate=August 5, 2014|date=June 9, 2014}}</ref> In May 2015, she announced her [[Las Vegas]] residency concert show, which commenced on January 20, 2016; the first of twenty initial dates. It takes place at [[Planet Hollywood Resort & Casino|Planet Hollywood]]'s [[The AXIS]] theater.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stutz|first1=Colin|title=Jennifer Lopez Announces Las Vegas Residency|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6561397/jennifer-lopez-announces-las-vegas-residency|work=Billboard |accessdate=May 18, 2015|date=May 12, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Feeney|first1=Nolan|title=Jennifer Lopez Announces 2016 Vegas Residency|url=http://time.com/3856958/jennifer-lopez-vegas-residency/|website=Time |accessdate=May 18, 2015|date=May 13, 2015}}</ref> The residency show is titled [[All I Have (residency)|All I Have]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez Reveals Title and Artwork for Vegas Show|url=http://lasvegas.cbslocal.com/2015/09/20/jennifer-lopez-reveals-title-and-artwork-for-vegas-show/|website=CBS Las Vegas|accessdate=September 20, 2015|date=September 20, 2015}}</ref> Extending her residency in Las Vegas, Lopez signed a three-year contract which will see her perform 120 shows.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Leach|first1=Robin|title=Review: J.Lo inks three-year contract; Pitbull, Ne-Yo, Ja Rule join her onstage|url=http://lasvegassun.com/vegasdeluxe/2016/jan/21/review-jlo-inks-three-year-contract-as-pitbull-ne/|website=[[Las Vegas Sun]]|publisher=[[Greenspun Media Group]]|accessdate=June 29, 2016|date=January 21, 2016}}</ref>
In March 2016, six years after announcing her departure, she announced her return to Epic Records, signing a multi-album deal with the label.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez Signs New Deal With Epic Records|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6897352/jennifer-lopez-signs-new-deal-with-epic-records|accessdate=March 2, 2016|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|agency=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|date=March 2, 2016|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6fipkjOKm|archivedate=March 2, 2016|location=United States}}</ref> Her first single since returning to Epic, "[[Ain't Your Mama]]", was released the following month.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rosen|first1=Christopher|title=Jennifer Lopez teases new single 'Ain't Your Mama'|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/04/04/jennifer-lopez-aint-your-mama|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |accessdate=April 7, 2016|date=April 4, 2016}}</ref> In July, Lopez released a single entitled "[[Love Make the World Go Round]]", a collaboration with [[Lin-Manuel Miranda]], which benefits victims of the [[2016 Orlando nightclub shooting]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Getz|first1=Dana|title=Jennifer Lopez, Lin-Manuel Miranda team for Orlando tribute 'Love Make the World Go Round'|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/07/07/jennifer-lopez-lin-manuel-miranda-orlando-love-make-world-go-round|website=Entertainment Weekly|publisher=Time Inc.|accessdate=July 7, 2016|date=July 7, 2016}}</ref> Later that month, Lopez announced a new dance competition series entitled ''World of Dance'', for which she serves as an executive producer. Created in partnership with [[World of Dance]], the series was greenlit by NBC with a straight-to-series order for ten episodes.<ref name="Variety July 2016">{{cite web|last1=Wagmeister|first1=Elizabeth|title=NBC Greenlights Reality Dance Competition Series from Jennifer Lopez|url=http://variety.com/2016/tv/news/world-of-dance-jennifer-lopez-competition-reality-nbc-1201817499/|website=Variety|publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]|accessdate=July 23, 2016|date=July 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Blistein|first1=Jon|title=Jennifer Lopez Dance Competition Headed to NBC|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/tv/news/jennifer-lopez-dance-competition-headed-to-nbc-w429924|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|publisher=Wenner Media|accessdate=July 23, 2016|date=July 20, 2016}}</ref>

In collaboration with [[Giuseppe Zanotti]], Lopez has designed a capsule collection of shoes and jewelry. ''Giuseppe for Jennifer Lopez'' will launch in January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Underwood|first1=Khalea|title=Jennifer Lopez Teams Up With Giuseppe Zanotti for ‘Bad Ass High Heels’ Collection|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-style/news/jennifer-lopez-and-giuseppe-zanotti-will-release-shoes-w431171|website=[[Us Weekly]]|publisher=Wenner Media|accessdate=July 28, 2016|date=July 27, 2016}}</ref>

==Personal life==

Lopez's personal life has attracted widespread media attention.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.redorbit.com/news/entertainment/235032/jlo_wins_moms_approval_by_working_with_redford/|title=J-Lo wins mom's approval by working with Redford - Redorbit|last=redOrbit|date=2005-09-08|website=Redorbit|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-18}}</ref> From February 22, 1997 to January 1998, she was married to Cuban waiter Ojani Noa.<ref name="A blow for J.Lo">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1391664/Jennifer-Lopezs-ex-husband-wins-legal-fight-release-embarrassing-home-video.html |title=Jennifer Lopez's ex-husband wins legal fight to release embarrassing home video &#124; Mail Online |work=Daily Mail |date=May 27, 2011 |accessdate=December 10, 2012}}</ref> Since their brief marriage, Lopez has endured legal troubles regarding Noa. In April 2006, she sued to prevent him from publishing a book about their marriage, contending that it violated their confidentiality agreement.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1528384/20060411/lopez_jennifer.jhtml?headlines=true |title=Jennifer Lopez Sues First Husband To Block Tell-All Book |author=Chris Harris |accessdate=January 16, 2007 |publisher=MTV News |date=April 11, 2006}}</ref> The following year, a court-appointed arbitrator issued a permanent injunction forbidding Noa from "criticizing, denigrating, casting in a negative light or otherwise disparaging" Lopez. She was awarded $545,000 in compensatory damages and Noa was ordered to hand over all copies of materials related to the book to Lopez or her attorney.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/people/jlo-wins-payout-from-ex-over-tellall-memoir/2007/08/09/1186530500816.html | title=J-Lo Wins Payout From Ex | accessdate=August 28, 2007 |work=Sydney Morning Herald | date=August 9, 2007}}</ref> A lawsuit regarding a compromising private honeymoon video in Noa's possession is presently running.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2013/06/13/jennifer-lopezs-ex-holding-out-for-more-money-in-honeymoon-video-lawsuit/ |title=Jennifer Lopez's Ex Holding Out For More Money In Honeymoon Video Lawsuit &#124; Fox News Latino |publisher=Fox News Latino|date=June 13, 2013 |accessdate=June 18, 2013}}</ref>

While working on her first album ''On the 6'', Lopez began dating record producer and rapper [[Sean Combs]]. On December 27, 1999, the couple were arrested along with two others in connection with a shooting outside the [[Times Square]] Club in [[New York City|New York]]. They were charged with criminal possession of a weapon as well as stolen property. Lopez was soon exonerated, having had nothing to do with the crime.<ref>{{cite web|last=Rosen|first=Craig|title=Jennifer Lopez Not Down With Guns|url=http://www.music.yahoo.ca/read/news/12056140|publisher=Yahoo! Music News|accessdate=April 8, 2013|date=January 14, 2000}}</ref> However, Combs was charged and indicted by a [[Manhattan]] [[grand jury]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Rosen|first=Craig|title=Jennifer Lopez 'Surprised And Saddened' By Puffy Indictment|url=http://www.music.yahoo.ca/read/news/12063159|publisher=Yahoo! Music News|accessdate=April 8, 2013|date=January 14, 2000}}</ref> After leaving Combs, Lopez developed a relationship with former back-up dancer [[Cris Judd]], whom she was married to from September 29, 2001 to June 2002.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jennifer Lopez, husband Cris Judd split after 8 months of marriage|newspaper=San Jose Mercury News |date=June 8, 2002|location=California}}</ref> Following her second divorce, she commenced a high-profile relationship with actor and director [[Ben Affleck]], whom she became engaged to in November 2002.<ref>{{cite news|last=Silverman|first=Stephen|title=Ben's Proposal 'Beautiful,' Says Lopez|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,624998,00.html|work=[[People (American magazine)|People]] |accessdate=October 20, 2012|date=November 11, 2002}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Williams|first=Jeanne|title=J. Lo, Ben make first appearance as fiances|newspaper=[[USA Today]] |date=December 10, 2002|page=2}}</ref> The media began to refer to them as "Bennifer", and they became a prominent [[supercouple]] in the media and popular culture. Bennifer became a popular term, which was eventually entered into [[Urban Dictionary|urban dictionaries]] and [[neologism]] dictionaries as notable,<ref>{{cite web|title=Neologisms. These are neologisms collected by an undergraduate linguistics class at Rice University during the fall of 2003|publisher=Rice University |accessdate=June 22, 2007|url=http://www.ruf.rice.edu/~kemmer/Words04/neologisms/a.html#b}}</ref> as the name blend started the trend of other celebrity couples being referred to by the combination of their first names.<ref name="Celebrity Name Game">{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,1133516,00.html |title=Celebrity Name Game |work=People |date=November 23, 2005 |accessdate=July 7, 2012}}</ref> The couple postponed their nuptials indefinitely a day prior to the planned ceremony in September 2003, citing the media's interference with the event as the reason.<ref>{{cite news|title=Media in frenzy over postponed 'Bennifer' wedding|url=http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2003/09/12/1063341766856.html|accessdate=February 25, 2012|newspaper=The Age |date=September 13, 2003|location=Los Angeles}}</ref>

[[File:Time 100 Jennifer Lopez and Marc Anthony.jpg|thumb|right|Anthony and Lopez, 2006]]

Following her break-up with Affleck in January 2004, Lopez began dating long-time friend [[Marc Anthony]] (real name: Marco Antonio Muñiz). The couple wed that June,<ref>{{cite news |author=Andrew Dansby |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/j-lo-marc-anthony-marry-20040607 |title=J.Lo, Marc Anthony Marry &#124; Music News |work=Rolling Stone |date=June 7, 2004 |accessdate=April 1, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Wedding highlights J.Lo's true talent: getting us talking|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=AASB&p_theme=aasb&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=1031F01295C1112D&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|accessdate=February 25, 2012 | newspaper=Austin American-Statesman |date=June 9, 2004}}</ref> and lived in [[Brookville, New York]].<ref>[http://hollywoodlife.com/2011/07/19/jennifer-lopez-marc-anthony-divorce-properties-houses-brookville-new-york/ Jennifer Lopez & Marc Anthony Own $5.75 Million Worth Of Property In New York: Who Will Get It?] Retrieved 2014-09-05</ref> Two men attempted to ransom a private wedding video that was stolen from the couple for one million dollars; however, they were arraigned in Manhattan Criminal Court on charges of conspiracy, attempted grand larceny and possession of stolen property.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://msnbc.msn.com/id/10643569/site/todayshow/ns/today-entertainment/t/lopez-anthony-wedding-video-leads-arrests/ |title=Lopez-Anthony wedding video leads to arrests&nbsp;– Entertainment&nbsp;– Celebrities |publisher=MSNBC |accessdate=April 1, 2012}}</ref> On November 7, 2007, during the final night of their co-headlining tour, Lopez and Anthony officially confirmed that they were expecting their first child.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/7084486.stm|title=Singer Lopez confirms pregnancy|publisher=BBC News |date=November 8, 2007|accessdate=November 9, 2007}}</ref> The announcement ended months of speculation over the pregnancy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollyscoop.com/jennifer-lopez/roberto-cavalli-confirms-jlos-pregnancy.html |title=Roberto Cavalli Confirms J.Lo's Pregnancy&nbsp;– Jennifer Lopez |publisher=Hollyscoop.com |accessdate=March 21, 2012 }}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> Her father confirmed that the couple were expecting twins, revealing that it runs in the family: "My sister also had twins, so it's a hereditary thing."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nme.com/news/jennifer-lopez/34139 |title=Jennifer Lopez expecting twins |work=[[NME]] |date=February 6, 2008 |accessdate=November 12, 2012}}</ref>

Lopez gave birth to a son, Maximilian David and a daughter, Emme Maribel, in [[Long Island]], New York on February 22, 2008.<ref name="Welcomes Twins">{{cite news |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20171851,00.html|date=February 22, 2008|title=Jennifer Lopez & Marc Anthony Welcome Twins!|work=People |accessdate=February 22, 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20181407,00.html|title=Jennifer Lopez & Marc Anthony Reveal Baby Names|work=People  |accessdate=February 29, 2008}}</ref> The twins were introduced in the March 11, 2008 issue of ''People'', for which the magazine paid a reported $6&nbsp;million&nbsp;— the photographs of the twins became [[List of most expensive celebrity photographs|the most expensive celebrity picture ever taken]] at the time.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.forbes.com/2009/07/01/michael-jackson-magazine-business-media-jackson.html |title=Jackson Pic Won't Make List Of Priciest Celeb Photos |work=Forbes |accessdate=March 21, 2012 |first=Lacey |last=Rose}}</ref> Three years later in July 2011, the couple announced their split, with Anthony filing for divorce in April 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2012/04/11/jennifer-lopez-divorce-marc-anthony-jlo/ |title=Jennifer Lopez Divorce&nbsp;— Marc Anthony Files Divorce From JLo |publisher=Hollywood Life |date=April 11, 2012 |accessdate=June 18, 2013}}</ref> Their divorce was finalized on June 16, 2014, with Lopez retaining primary physical custody of the two children.<ref>{{cite web | url= http://www.tmz.com/2014/06/18/jlo-jennifer-lopez-marc-anthony-divorce-paparazzi/|title=Jennifer Lopez & Marc Anthony's Divorce Has An Anti-Paparazzi Clause| date= June 18, 2014| publisher=[[TMZ.com]]| accessdate= April 13, 2016 | quote=The divorce — 2 years in the making —became official Monday [June 16, 2014]. | archivedate=June 19, 2014| archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20140619005100/http://www.tmz.com/2014/06/18/jlo-jennifer-lopez-marc-anthony-divorce-paparazzi/ | deadurl=no}}</ref> On December 31, 2014, she legally changed her name back to Jennifer Lopez, dropping Anthony's last name (Muñiz).<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ctvnews.ca/entertainment/jennifer-lopez-gets-her-name-changed-1.2171025 |title=Jennifer Lopez gets her name changed &#124; Entertainment & Showbiz from CTV News |publisher=Ctvnews.ca |date=2015-01-03 |accessdate=2015-05-15}}</ref>

In October 2011, Lopez began dating her former back-up dancer Casper Smart.<ref>{{cite news |last=Nudd |first=Tim |url=http://www.people.com/article/jennifer-lopez-casper-smart-split |title=Jennifer Lopez and Casper Smart Split - Breakups, Casper Smart, Jennifer Lopez, which months later the two have rekindled. |work=People |accessdate=2014-07-20}}</ref> They temporarily ended their relationship in June 2014, but reconciled several months later.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez Confirms Her Relationship with Casper Smart – But 'There's No Wedding'|url=http://www.people.com/article/jennifer-lopez-no-wedding-casper-smart|website=People}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Beau Casper Smart on Relationship with Jennifer Lopez: 'We're Just Having a Good Time'|url=http://www.people.com/article/jennifer-lopez-casper-smart-having-good-time|website=People}}</ref>

==Artistry==

===Musical style===

{{Listen
| pos = right
| filename = Waiting for Tonight.ogg
| title = "Waiting for Tonight"
| description = A twenty-five-second sample of "[[Waiting for Tonight]]". It is a [[dance-pop]] party song that incorporates [[Latin American music|Latin]] and [[Europop|European]] influences.<ref name="Garvin">{{cite web|last1=Blumentrath|first1=Jan|title=Interview with Michael Garvin|url=http://hitquarters.com/index.php3?page=intrview/2005/July24_5_50_38.html|publisher=Hitquarters.com|accessdate=January 6, 2015|date=July 24, 2005}}</ref><ref name="Variety" />
}}

Over the course of her career, Lopez's music has covered a wide range of genres including Latin pop, dance, R&B, hip hop, rock, funk, house and salsa. According to author Ed Morales, her music explores both the "romantic innocence of Latin music" and hip hop.<ref>{{cite book|last=Morales|first=Ed|title=The Latin Beat: The Rhythms And Roots Of Latin Music From Bossa Nova To Salsa And Beyond|year=2003|publisher=Da Capo Press|isbn=078673020X|page=163}}</ref> While heavily influenced by Latin musical styles ranging from [[salsa (music)|salsa]] to [[Bachata (music)|bachata]], it was the 1979 hip hop song "[[Rapper's Delight]]" by hip hop trio [[The Sugarhill Gang]] that inspired her career. On her first album ''On the 6'' (1999), Lopez fused Latin music together with the hip hop sound she loved, which she described as being [[Latin soul]].<ref name="Woog08">{{harvnb|Woog|2008}}</ref>

Much of her early music was centered around dance, funk, urban and Latin-influenced music.<ref name="Thru1">{{cite web|last=Dinh|first=James|title=J.Lo Contemplates 'Love' (And Love?) Through The Years|url=http://newsroom.mtv.com/2011/05/03/jlo-contemplates-love-and-love-through-the-years/|publisher=MTV Newsroom |accessdate=April 7, 2013|date=May 3, 2011}}</ref><ref name="Back">{{cite news|last=Morales|first=Ed|title=It's Not La Vida Loca to Her|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1999/may/30/entertainment/ca-42339|accessdate=March 11, 2012|newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=March 30, 1999}}</ref><ref name="DVD Talk">{{cite web|url=http://www.dvdtalk.com/reviews/6295/jennifer-lopez-on-the-6/ |title=Jennifer Lopez: On The 6 : DVD Talk Review of the Audio |publisher=[[DVD Talk]] |accessdate=July 11, 2012}}</ref> With her second album ''J.Lo'' (2001), Lopez wrote more personal songs, while retaining the same sound as her first.<ref name="Personal">{{cite web|title=A whole lotta Lopez|url=http://jam.canoe.ca/Movies/Artists/L/Lopez_Jennifer/2001/01/21/759920.html|publisher=Canoe|accessdate=April 12, 2013|date=January 21, 2001}}</ref> Empowerment and sex are among the album's themes.<ref name="Slant Magazine">{{cite web|last=Cinquemani|first=Sal|title=Jennifer Lopez: J.Lo|url=http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/jennifer-lopez-j-lo/208|publisher=[[Slant Magazine]]|accessdate=April 13, 2013|date=February 11, 2001}}</ref> A departure from her previous albums, ''This Is Me... Then'' (2002) evokes 1970s [[soul music]], with Lopez stating that: "This record has a little bit of that nostalgia in it", while its lyrical content was influenced by her relationship with Ben Affleck. This is most evident within the song "Dear Ben".<ref name=guardian>{{cite news|author=Betty Clarke |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2002/nov/29/popandrock.artsfeatures2 |title=CD: Jennifer Lopez: This Is Me...Then &#124; Culture |newspaper=The Guardian |date= November 29, 2002|accessdate=March 30, 2012 |location=London}}</ref><ref name="RockBlock">{{cite web|title=J.Lo: The Rock And The Block|url=http://www.mtv.com/bands/l/lopez_jennifer/news_feature_021108/index2.jhtml#|publisher=MTV |accessdate=April 3, 2013}}http://www.mtv.com/bands/l/lopez_jennifer/news_feature_021108/</ref> ''Rebirth'' (2005) explored more of a pop rock and funk sound, with a strong utilization of percussion and horns.<ref name=yahoor>{{cite web|url=http://voices.yahoo.com/jennifer-lopez-rebirth-album-review-68857.html |title=Jennifer Lopez: Rebirth (Album Review) |publisher=Yahoo! Voices |date=March 1, 2005 |accessdate=April 29, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140729044240/http://voices.yahoo.com/jennifer-lopez-rebirth-album-review-68857.html |archivedate=July 29, 2014 }}</ref>{{unreliable source?|date=October 2015}} ''Como Ama una Mujer'' (2007), her first full Spanish-language album, includes introspective lyrics about love, heartache and self-loathing. It has a more softer sound than her previous works.<ref name="Reed">{{cite news|url=http://boston.com/ae/music/cd_reviews/articles/2007/03/27/lopez_turns_the_lights_down_low |title=Jennifer Lopez goes unabashedly romantic with 'Como Ama una Mujer'|work=[[The Boston Globe]] |date=March 27, 2007 |accessdate=June 3, 2012 |first=James |last=Reed}}</ref> ''Brave'' (2007) and ''Love?'' (2011) are rooted more in a dance music direction.<ref name="Allmusic Brave">{{cite web|last=Erlewine |first=Stephen Thomas |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/brave-r1208434 |title=Brave&nbsp;– Jennifer Lopez |publisher=[[AllMusic]]. Rovi Corporation |accessdate=November 10, 2011}}</ref> Songs from ''Love?'' such as "[[Until It Beats No More]]" and "[[One Love (Jennifer Lopez song)|One Love]]" are also deeply personal songs.<ref>{{cite news |last=Markovitz |first=Adam |title=Jennifer Lopez&nbsp;– Love? (album review) |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20485119,00.html |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=April 27, 2011 |accessdate=May 28, 2011}}</ref> Lopez describes her music as autobiographical.<ref>{{cite web|title=How Jennifer Lopez Turned Hitting 'Rock Bottom' Into A Memoir|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/11/05/jennifer-lopez-_n_6107300.html|website=The Huffington Post|accessdate=January 1, 2015|date=November 5, 2014}}</ref>

Lopez has been influenced by artists such as [[Tina Turner]], [[James Brown]], [[Michael Jackson]], [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]] and [[Barbra Streisand]].<ref name="10 Questions for Lopez">{{cite news |url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1673250,00.html |title=10 Questions for Jennifer Lopez |work=Time |date=October 18, 2007 |accessdate=August 18, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Miller|first=Prairie|title=NY Rock Interview with Jennifer Lopez|url=http://www.nyrock.com/interviews/2002/lopez_int3.asp |publisher=NY Rock |accessdate=February 12, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez 'graduated' as a singer while singing for hubby|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/jennifer-lopez-graduated-as-a-singer-while/558630/|newspaper=Indian Express}}</ref> Critics have considered Lopez's [[soubrette]] vocal type to be limited,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/pages/jenniferlopezx18x03x05 |title=Jennifer Lopez&nbsp;– Rebirth&nbsp;– Album Review |publisher=Contactmusic News |accessdate=April 1, 2012}}</ref><ref name=vocall>{{cite web|title=Jennifer Lopez finds her voice on new album|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2011/02/02/jennifer-lopez-finds-her-voice-on-new-album/#more-72798|work=Rap-Up |publisher=SpinMedia|accessdate=February 12, 2012}}</ref> and obscured by the production of her music, while remaining "radio-friendly".<ref>{{cite news |last=Henderling|first=Lisa|title=Revolutions|work=Vibe|date=December 2007|volume= 15| issue = 12|page=107 |issn=1070-4701}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' observed: "Instead of strained vocal pyrotechnics, Lopez sticks to the understated R&B murmur of a round-the-way superstar who doesn't need to belt because she knows you're already paying attention [...] She makes a little va-va and a whole lot of voom go a long way."<ref name="Rolling">{{cite news |last=Sheffield|first=Rob|title=On the 6 {{!}} Album Reviews|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/on-the-6-19990708|work=Rolling Stone |accessdate=April 8, 2013|date=July 8, 1999}}</ref> Meanwhile, [[AllMusic]]'s [[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] called her voice "slight" and wrote: "Lopez was never, ever about singing; she was about style, particularly the kind that passes for fashionable at glitzy high-rise discos."<ref name="Erlewine">{{cite web|author=Stephen Thomas Erlewine|url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=love-r2142805|pure_url=yes}}|title= Love?&nbsp;– Jennifer Lopez |publisher=[[Allmusic]]|date=April 19, 2011|accessdate=May 3, 2011}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' criticized her vocal performance for lacking the trademark "husky-voiced voluptuousness" she has in her films.<ref name="EW">{{cite news|last=Browne|first=David|title=On the 6 (1999)|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,273612,00.html|work=Entertainment Weekly |accessdate=April 7, 2013|date=June 4, 1999}}</ref> ''[[The Baltimore Sun]]'' regards Lopez as having a "breathy" stylistic range, but lacking personality.<ref>{{cite news |last=Considine|first=J.D.|title=Actress Jennifer Lopez can sing, but it isn't enough|newspaper=The Baltimore Sun|date=June 3, 1999 |issn=1930-8965}}</ref>

===Dance and stage===

Considered one of dance's "greatest success stories",<ref name="Variety July 2016" /> Lopez has felt an emotional connection to dance since her childhood.<ref name="Dance buzz">{{cite web|last=Vena |first=Jocelyn |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1659131/jennifer-lopez-on-the-floor-video.jhtml |title=Jennifer Lopez's 'On The Floor' Video Creates 'Dance Buzz'&nbsp;– Music, Celebrity, Artist News |publisher=MTV News |date=March 3, 2011 |accessdate=May 31, 2013}}</ref> Growing up, she specialized in ballet, jazz and flamenco dance genres.<ref name="Shall We Dance? - Interview">{{cite web|last=Boccard|first=Sophia|title=Jennifer Lopez Interview for Shall We Dance?|url=http://www.thecinemasource.com/blog/interviews/jennifer-lopez-interview-for-shall-we-dance/|publisher=The Cinema Source |accessdate=June 30, 2013|date=January 28, 2008}}</ref> Her career commenced on the variety television sketch comedy series ''[[In Living Color]]'', where she was a part of an ethnically diverse dance group labeled The Fly Girls.<ref name="Hip Hop Dance">{{cite book|last=Rajakumar|first=Mohanalakshmi|title=The American Dancefloor: Hip Hop Dance|year=2012|publisher=Abc-Clio|isbn=0313378452|pages=78, 79|edition=Illustrated}}</ref> Lopez briefly served as a back-up dancer to recording artist [[Janet Jackson]], who she claimed to have a considerable influence over her choreography. After beginning her own recording career, Lopez's provocatively choreographed debut music video for "If You Had My Love" allowed her to become a dominant figure on [[MTV]] Networks worldwide.<ref>{{cite news |title=Asia Pacific|work=Billboard|date=August 7, 1999|volume= 111| issue = g32 |issn=0006-2510}}</ref> Since, Lopez has become well known for her body-emphasizing music videos such as "[[Waiting for Tonight#Music video|Waiting for Tonight]]", "[[I'm Glad]]", "[[Dance Again#Music video|Dance Again]]" and "[[Booty (song)|Booty]]" among others, some of which have been the subject of controversy and scrutiny.<ref>{{cite news |last=Costanza|first=Ashley Justine|title=Jennifer Lopez's 'Dance Again' Video Stirs Controversy: Her Five Trashiest Videos|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/jennifer-lopezs-dance-again-video-stirs-controversy-her-five-trashiest-videos-435170|work=International Business Times |accessdate=June 30, 2013|date=April 9, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Nobody Puts J.Lo's Booty in a Box|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/151961_jennifer_lopez_defends_her_booty_video_talks_scary_car_accident/|website=ETOnline |accessdate=December 27, 2014|date=October 1, 2014}}</ref> For the film ''Shall We Dance?'' (2004), Lopez learned a new genre of dance: ballroom.<ref>{{cite news |title=Director hopes audience will find 'Dance'|newspaper=The New Tribune|date=October 16, 2004 |location=Tacoma, Washington}}</ref> Lopez often includes dance routines in her music videos.<ref>{{cite book|title=Sexual Teens, Sexual Media: Investigating Mediás Influence on Adolescent Sexuality|year=2002|publisher=Routledge|isbn=0805834907|page=260|author1=Jane Delano Brown |author2=Jeanne R. Steele |author3=Kim Walsh-Childers }}</ref>

Author Priscilla Peña Ovalle stated in ''Dance and the Hollywood Latina: Race, Sex and Stardom'' (2011) that Lopez was one of the Latin female stars who "used dance to gain agency as working performers with mainstream careers, yet many of their roles paradoxically racialized and sexualized their bodies".<ref name="Dance Hollywood Latina">{{cite book|last=Peña Ovalle|first=Priscilla|title=Dance and the Hollywood Latina: Race, Sex, and Stardom|year=2011|publisher=Rutgers University Press|isbn=0813548802|pages=3–4}}</ref> Troy Patterson of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' also observed that she used her body for emphasis on stage, "She turned herself out as the fly girl hyperversion of postfeminist power, flaunting her control by toying with the threat of excess. In consequence, her star went supernova."<ref>{{cite news|last=Patterson|first=Troy|title=Rock Frock|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,92259,00.html|work=Entertainment Weekly |accessdate=June 30, 2013|date=December 19, 2000}}</ref> Lopez and fellow entertainer [[Shakira]] are known for their signature moves, which include "clock-wise pivoting with salsa hip circles and sequential torso undulations".<ref>{{cite book|last=Potuoglu-Cook|first=Oyku|title=Night Shifts: Moral, Economic, and Cultural Politics of Turkish Belly Dance|year=2008|publisher=ProQuest|isbn=0549541306|page=167}}</ref> Lopez is recognized for energetic and provocative stage performances, which have at times received scrutiny.<ref>{{cite web|last= Gruttadaro |first=Andrew |url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2013/05/27/selena-gomez-sexy-performances-miley-cyrus-rihanna-pics/ |title=Selena Gomez's Sexy Performances & More Hot Hollywood Stage Sirens |publisher=Hollywood Life |date=May 27, 2013 |accessdate=May 31, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Solomons |first=Tarryn |url=http://www.iol.co.za/tonight/in-your-face-marc-1.1183920 |title=In your face Marc |publisher=IOL Tonight|date=November 22, 2011 |accessdate=May 31, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://popcrush.com/john-legend-questo-jennifer-lopez-fiat/ |title=John Legend + Questo Ridicule Jennifer Lopez Over 'Shameless' Fiat Plug |publisher=Popcrush |accessdate=May 31, 2013}}</ref> She often includes costumes such as bodysuits as part of her performance.<ref>{{cite news|author=Amelia Proud |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2214393/Jennifer-Lopez-cuts-devastatingly-curvy-silhouette-sheer-rhinestone-encrusted-bodysuit.html |title=Jennifer Lopez Cuts a Devastatingly Curvy Silhouette in Sheer Rhinestone-encrusted Bodysuit |newspaper=Daily Mail |date=October 8, 2012 |accessdate=May 31, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/11/21/jennifer-lopez-bodysuit-ama_n_1106714.html |title=Jennifer Lopez' Bodysuit At The 2011 American Music Awards (Photos)|publisher=The Huffington Post |date=November 21, 2011 |accessdate=May 31, 2013 |first=Christina |last=Anderson}}</ref> While being noted to [[lip sync]] in the early stages of career, Lopez's Dance Again World Tour was praised for showcasing live vocals and choreography synchronously.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lip syncing takes the fun out of seeing an artist live|newspaper=Contra Costa Times|date=June 21, 2002}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Fuller |first=Bonnie |url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2012/12/05/jennifer-lopez-dance-again-tour-divorce-marc-anthony/ |title=Jennifer Lopez 'Dance Again' Tour&nbsp;— Why She Had to Divorce Marc Anthony |publisher=Hollywood Life |date=December 5, 2012 |accessdate=May 31, 2013}}</ref><ref name="filipino">{{cite web|last=Concepcion|first=Pocholo|title=JLo enchants capacity crowd at MOA Arena concert|url=http://entertainment.inquirer.net/69407/jlo-enchants-capacity-crowd-at-moa-arena-concert|work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |accessdate=November 27, 2012|date=November 27, 2012}}</ref> In May 2013, Lopez's performance on the finale of the television series ''[[Britain's Got Talent]]'' was deemed inappropriate for family-friendly television, and drew viewer complaints to [[Ofcom]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2332453/Jennifer-Lopezs-raunchy-Britains-Got-Talent-performance-blasted-inappropriate-viewers.html |title=Jennifer Lopez's raunchy Britain's Got Talent performance blasted as 'inappropriate' by viewers |newspaper=Daily Mail |date= May 29, 2013|accessdate=May 31, 2013 |first1=Hanna |last1=Flint |first2=Louise |last2=Saunders}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com.au/british-tv/s107/britains-got-talent/news/a486003/jennifer-lopez-britains-got-talent-producers-said-to-wear-outfit.html |title=Jennifer Lopez: 'Britain's Got Talent producers said to wear outfit' |publisher=Digital Spy |accessdate=May 31, 2013}}</ref>

==Public image==

[[File:LG JSOSPP7061102.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Lopez waving the [[Puerto Rico|Puerto Rican]] flag in 2009]]

Speaking of Lopez's image, Andrew Barker of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' observed: "Despite a carefully cultivated image as an imperious pop empress in ludicrously expensive outfits, her signature hits bear the titles "I'm Real" and "Jenny From the Block". She managed the perilous transition from actress to music star without ever seeming to pick either as a primary gig. She established herself as an oft-provocative sex symbol while her demeanor made it abundantly clear that she's not asking you to come hither."<ref name="Variety">{{cite news|last=Barker|first=Andrew|title=Jennifer Lopez Receives Star for Music on Hollywood Walk of Fame|url=http://variety.com/2013/scene/features/jennifer-lopez-receives-star-for-music-on-hollywood-walk-of-fame-1200493728/|work=Variety |accessdate=June 25, 2013|date=June 20, 2013}}</ref> In 2002, Lynette Holloway of ''[[The New York Times]]'' described Lopez as overexposed. She wrote: "Forgive yourself if you are seeing Jennifer Lopez in your sleep. She is everywhere." Holloway noted her image to be "a dash of ''ghetto fabulousness''" and "middle-class respectability" for mass appeal.<ref>{{cite news |last=Holloway|first=Lynette|title=Keeping J. Lo in Spotlight Has Risks for Her Career As Well as Rich Rewards|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=December 9, 2002|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2002/12/09/business/keeping-j-lo-in-spotlight-has-risks-for-her-career-as-well-as-rich-rewards.html|accessdate=June 30, 2013}}</ref> Lopez is considered an [[pop icon|icon of popular culture]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2005/10/prweb298759.htm |title=The Biggest Latin Vibe Sweeping America Is Up for Sale? |publisher=PRWeb |accessdate=November 12, 2012}}</ref> Television presenter [[Ray Martin (television presenter)|Ray Martin]] describes her as a "showbiz phenomenon".<ref>{{cite web|last=Martin|first=Ray|title=J-Lo|url=http://sixtyminutes.ninemsn.com.au/stories/raymartin/304846/j-lo|accessdate=February 28, 2012|date=October 11, 2007}}</ref> Lopez has developed an image as a sex symbol and "one of the most desirable women on the planet".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2016603/Jennifer-Lopez-divorce-Controlling-Marc-Anthony-hated-J-Lo-sex-symbol.html |title=Jennifer Lopez divorce: Controlling Marc Anthony 'hated J-Lo being a sex symbol' |work=Daily Mail |date=July 20, 2011 |accessdate=August 19, 2012}}</ref> She is well known for her curvaceous figure,<ref>{{cite news |author=Katherine Ormerod |url=http://www.graziadaily.co.uk/fashion/archive/2012/04/30/the-rise-of-the-super-bum--kim-kardashian--nikki-minaj---jlo-show-how-to-dress-y.htm |title=The Rise of the Super Bum: Kim Kardashian, Nicki Minaj & Jennifer Lopez Show How to Dress Your Booty &#124; Grazia Fashion |publisher=''Grazia'' |date=April 30, 2012 |accessdate=August 19, 2012}}</ref> which was the inspiration for [[Sir Mix-a-Lot]]'s 1992 hit "[[Baby Got Back]]".<ref>{{cite web|title=Sir Mix-A-Lot Says 'Baby Got Back' Is About Jennifer Lopez|url=http://www.spin.com/articles/sir-mix-a-lot-says-baby-got-back-is-about-jennifer-lopez/|website=Spin|publisher=SpinMedia|accessdate=January 4, 2015|date=November 13, 2014}}</ref> Widely recognized and celebrated for her figure, she has been credited with allowing women with curvaceous figures to be accepted.<ref>{{cite book|title=Mi Voz, Mi Vida/ My Voice, My Life: Latino College Students Tell Their Life Stories|year=2007|publisher=Cornwell University Press|isbn=0801473861|page=179|author1=Andrew Garrod |author2=Robert Kilkenny |author3=Christina Gómez }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Marisa Meltzer:For Posteriors' Sake|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/18/fashion/more-women-seeking-curvaceous-posteriors.html?_r=1|date=2014-09-17}}</ref>

[[Details (magazine)|''Details'']] magazine named Lopez the "Sexiest Woman of the Year" in 1998,<ref>{{cite news|last=Halza|first=George Halza|title=Jennifer Lopez named sexiest woman of the year|newspaper=[[Reading Eagle]]|date=November 16, 1998|page=5}}</ref> and she led ''[[FHM]]''{{'}}s "100 Sexiest Women" list twice.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com/girls/covergirls/jennifer-lopez |title=''FHM''&nbsp;– Jennifer Lopez |publisher=Fhm.com |accessdate=March 10, 2012}}</ref> In 2011, she was named "[[People Magazine's 100 Most Beautiful People|The Most Beautiful Woman]]" by [[People (American magazine)|''People'']].<ref>{{cite news |last=Jordan|first=Julie|title=Jennifer Lopez: Being Beautiful Is 'Part of My Job'|url=http://www.people.com/people/package/article/0,,20360857_20481259,00.html |work=People |accessdate=January 29, 2012|date=April 13, 2011}}</ref> The following year, [[VH1]] ranked her the fourth on their list of "100 Sexiest Artists",<ref>{{cite web|author=Bené Viera |url=http://www.vh1.com/music/tuner/2013-03-05/vh1-100-sexiest-artists-complete-list/97/ |title=VH1′s 100 Sexiest Artists [Complete List&#93;&nbsp;– &#124; VH1 Tuner |publisher=VH-1 |date=March 5, 2013 |accessdate=April 19, 2013}}</ref> while [[Vibe (magazine)|''Vibe'']] magazine named her the most "lustable" celebrity of the past twenty years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vibe.com/article/big-list-issue-19-most-lustable-celebs-93 |title=The 19 Most Lustable Celebs Since '93 |publisher=Vibe |date=April 17, 2013 |accessdate=May 31, 2013}}</ref> In 2014, Lopez stated, "There's this funny notion in America that you can't be a mom and be sexy (...) It's the craziest thing I've ever heard... The truth is that women can be sexy until the day they die."<ref name="HuffPost Latino"/>

Lopez is a [[Tabloid journalism|tabloid]] fixture<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lansky|first1=Sam|title=Jennifer Lopez Is Back On Top With 'Love?' Which Is Exactly Where She Deserves To Be|url=http://buzzworthy.mtv.com/2012/04/19/jennifer-lopez-love-on-the-floor-dance-again/|accessdate=January 28, 2015|work=[[MTV]]|publisher=[[Viacom]]|date=April 19, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Johnson|first1=Steve|title=Will Lopez, Tyler be good for 'American Idol'?|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2010-09-22/entertainment/chi-100922-american-idol-judges-strengths_1_kara-dioguardi-steven-tyler-classic-rock|accessdate=January 28, 2015|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|publisher=[[Tribune Publishing]]|date=September 22, 2010}}</ref> and has admitted to having a "less-than-perfect" public image.<ref>{{cite web|last=Saney|first=Daniel|title=J.Lo blames films for bad public image|url=http://www.digitalspy.com.au/showbiz/news/a19076/jlo-blames-films-for-bad-public-image.html|publisher=Digital Spy |accessdate=June 26, 2013|date=February 8, 2005}}</ref> The media often draw comparisons between Lopez and actress [[Elizabeth Taylor]], due to her numerous failed relationships.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vibe Media Group|date=July 2003|work=Vibe|publisher=Vibe Media Group|issue=7|volume=11|issn=1070-4701}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Hampson|first=Katie|title=Is J-Lo the new Liz Taylor?|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-305683/Is-J-Lo-new-Liz-Taylor.html|work=Daily Mail |accessdate=September 24, 2013|date=June 8, 2004}}</ref> In fact, Lopez has been dubbed a "modern-day Liz Taylor" by the media.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lopez doesn't mind Liz link|newspaper=The Age|date=December 27, 2002}}</ref> Lynn Hirschberg of ''[[W (magazine)|W]]'' compared her glamorous public persona to that of Taylor.<ref name="W2013">{{cite web|last=Hirschberg|first=Lynn|title=Jennifer Lopez: Dream Girl|url=http://www.wmagazine.com/people/celebrities/2013/07/jennifer-lopez-august-2013-cover/|work=W |accessdate=July 10, 2013|date=July 9, 2013}}</ref> Her style is described by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''{{'}}s Lauren Savage as scantily clad.<ref name="Scla">{{cite web|last=Savage|first=Lauren|title=J.Lo Plays Gender-Bending Boxer for V Magazine Cover|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-hook/502987/jlo-plays-gender-bending-boxer-for-v-magazine-cover|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=August 20, 2012|date=February 29, 2012}}</ref> Lopez has been criticized by the animal rights organization [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals|PETA]] for inclusion of fur in her fashion lines and outfits.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.peta.org/b/thepetafiles/archive/2011/08/04/how-low-will-j_2d00_lo-go_3f00_.aspx |title=PETA: How Low Will J-Lo Go? |publisher=PETA.org |accessdate=December 5, 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111023225651/http://www.peta.org/b/thepetafiles/archive/2011/08/04/How-Low-Will-J_2D00_Lo-Go_3F00_.aspx |archivedate=October 23, 2011}}</ref> She has received a bad reputation as being a demanding "diva",<ref>{{cite news |title=Demanding diva Jennifer Lopez bans domestic staff from speaking to her|url=http://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/demanding-diva-jennifer-lopez-bans-domestic-staff-from-speaking-to-her-8134190.html|work=[[Evening Standard]]|accessdate=January 8, 2013|date=September 13, 2012}}</ref> but she constantly refutes this.<ref name="ga23">{{cite news|title='I started going grey at 23,' admits Jennifer Lopez as she is crowned World's Most Beautiful Woman|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1376527/Jennifer-Lopez-tops-Most-Beautiful-list-People-magazine-2011.html|work=[[Daily Mail]] |accessdate=January 8, 2013|date=April 14, 2011}}</ref>

==Legacy and cultural influence==
{{see also|List of awards and nominations received by Jennifer Lopez}}

Lopez is regarded as the most influential Hispanic performer in the United States, having been credited with breaking racial barriers in the entertainment industry.<ref name=rantrack /><ref name=leading1 /> ''[[The Record (Waterloo Region)|The Record]]'' newspaper observed that she was responsible for the introduction of a Hispanic presence in the film industry.<ref name=therecord>{{cite news |last=Pearlman|first=Cindy|title=For the record; Very hot and ambitious actress Jennifer Lopez has music on her mind|newspaper=[[The Record (Waterloo Region)|The Record]] |ISSN=0824-5150|date=August 14, 1999|location=Kitchener, Ontario}}</ref> In ''Icons of American Popular Culture: From P.T. Barnum to Jennifer Lopez'' (2009), author Robert C. Cotrell describes Lopez as the Hispanic version of [[Oprah Winfrey]], calling her a "multidimensional artist who had turned into a financial powerhouse".<ref name="hhh">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=ZXRcV6k0F9sC&pg=PA221&lpg=PA221 |title=Icons of American Popular Culture: From P.T. Barnum to Jennifer Lopez |author=Robert C. Cottrell |publisher=M.E. Sharpe |page=221 |year=2009 |accessdate=March 10, 2012|isbn=978-0-7656-2835-0}}</ref> In 2012, ''[[Forbes]]'' opined that Lopez "may be the most powerful entertainer on the planet",<ref>{{cite news|last=Casserly|first=Meghan|title=The 10 Most Talked About Women of 2012|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/meghancasserly/2012/12/13/hillary-clinton-beyonce-10-most-talked-about-women-of-2012/|work=Forbes |accessdate=August 10, 2013|date=December 13, 2012}}</ref> and named her "the world's most powerful Latino celebrity".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Antunes|first1=Anderson|title=The World's Most Powerful Latino Celebrities|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/andersonantunes/2012/05/25/the-worlds-most-powerful-latino-celebrities/|accessdate=December 6, 2015|work=Forbes |date=May 25, 2012}}</ref> Lopez is the highest-paid actress of Hispanic descent, as well as the wealthiest actress in Hollywood as of 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://au.ibtimes.com/articles/483277/20130626/top-5-richest-actresses-hollywood.htm |title=Top 5 Richest Actresses In Hollywood |newspaper=International Business Times |date=June 26, 2013 |accessdate=August 10, 2013}}http://www.ibtimes.com/forbes-lists-top-100-most-powerful-celebrities-2013-oprah-winfrey-takes-number-one-spot-full-list</ref> Miriam Jiménez Román stated in ''The Afro-Latin Reader: History and Culture in the United States'' (2009) that "[she] was able to traverse the difficult racial boundaries".<ref>{{cite book|title=The Afro-Latin@ Reader: History and Culture in the United States|year=2009|publisher=Duke Press|isbn=0822391317|page=532|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mSJpaNVnazQC&pg=PT548&dq=Jennifer+Lopez+Latin&hl=en&sa=X&ei=GsTSUYibJ6G6iQfq2YDwCA&ved=0CEYQ6AEwBA|author1=Miriam Jiménez Román |author2=Juan Flores |accessdate=July 2, 2013}}</ref>

As a result of launching a career in music during the late 1990s, Lopez contributed to the "Latin explosion" that was occurring in entertainment at the time.<ref>{{cite news |last=Tarradell|first=Mario|title=Latin aftershocks Music's ethnic boom reshapes the Grammy landscape|newspaper=The Dallas Morning News|date=February 20, 2000}}</ref> She was featured on the cover of the first issue of ''[[Latina (magazine)|Latina]]'' in 1996, with editor Galina Espinoza stating in 2011, "there is no Latina magazine without Jennifer [Lopez], no recounting of modern Latina history without Jennifer, and no one who has more consistently represented Latinas than Jennifer."<ref>{{cite web|title= Latina View: Lessons Learned from 15 Years of Jennifer Lopez |url=http://www.latina.com/lifestyle/latina-view/latina-view-lessons-learned-15-years-jennifer-lopez}}</ref> The ''[[Daily Herald (Utah)|Daily Herald]]'' described Lopez as "crossover royalty".<ref>{{cite news |last=Gaurino|first=Mark|title=Wild percussion, guitars lead Los Lobos' fiesta Time Out Today!|newspaper=[[Daily Herald (Utah)|Daily Herald]] |page=2|date=August 11, 1999}}</ref> Around this time, the emphasis on Lopez's curvaceous figure grew; scholar Sean Redmond wrote that this was a sign of her role and social power in the cultural changes occurring in the United States.<ref>{{harvnb|Redmond|2007|pp=282–283}}</ref> In August 2005, ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' listed Lopez as one of the most influential Hispanics in America, remarking: "Why? Because over a decade ago, she was an anonymous background dancer on the second-rated sketch-comedy show. Today she's known by two syllables."<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tyrangiel|first1=Josh|title=25 Most Influential Hispanics in America|url=http://content.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,2008201_2008200_2008207,00.html|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |accessdate=December 6, 2015|date=August 22, 2015}}</ref> In February 2007, ''[[People en Español]]'' named her the most influential Hispanic entertainer.<ref name=leading1>{{cite news|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/peopleNews/idUSN0417833620070105|title=J.Lo tops list of most influential Hispanics|accessdate=February 12, 2007|agency=Reuters |date=January 4, 2007}}</ref> In 2013 [[Univision]] presented her with the World Icon Award in its Premios Juventud.<ref>{http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/07/19/jennifer-lopez-premios-juventud_n_3622993.html}</ref>

[[VH1]] ranked Lopez at number 15 on a list of "200 Greatest Pop Culture Icons",<ref>{{cite news |title=The 200 Greatest Pop Culture Icons Complete Ranked List|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/the-200-greatest-pop-culture-icons-complete-ranked-list-70807437.html|publisher=PRNewswire|accessdate=June 30, 2013}}</ref> number 16 on "100 Greatest Women In Music",<ref>{{cite web|last=Graham|first=Mark|title=VH1's 100 Greatest Women In Music|url=http://www.vh1.com/music/tuner/2012-02-13/vh1s-100-greatest-women-in-music-complete-list/|publisher=[[VH1]]|accessdate=February 29, 2012|date=February 13, 2012}}</ref> and number 21 on "50 Greatest Women of the Video Era".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vh1.com/shows/the_greatest/episode.jhtml?episodeID=66355 |title=Ep. 071 &#124; 50 Greatest Women of the Video Era |publisher=VH1 |accessdate=August 10, 2013}}</ref> Her album ''J to tha L-O! The Remixes'' was acknowledged by the ''[[Guinness World Records]]'' as the first number one remix album in the United States.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3186761.stm |title=Diaz tops actress pay list |accessdate=April 18, 2009 |date=August 27, 2004 |publisher=BBC News}}</ref> In 2010, Lopez was honored by the [[World Music Awards]] with the Legend Award for her contribution to the arts.<ref>{{cite news|author=Emily Sheridan |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1279581/World-Music-Awards-Jennifer-Lopez-shows-wild-animal-print-dresses.html |title=World Music Awards: Jennifer Lopez shows her wild side in two animal-print dresses |work=Daily Mail |date=May 19, 2010 |accessdate=August 12, 2012}}</ref> Lopez's return to prominence the following year with her single "On the Floor"—one of the [[List of best-selling singles|best-selling singles of all time]], and its music video recognized as the "Highest Viewed Female Music Video of All Time" by ''Guinness World Records'' in 2012—is regarded as one of the greatest musical comebacks in history.<ref name=comeback>{{cite news|last=Kennedy|first=Gerrick D.|title=Jennifer Lopez named 'world's greatest musical comeback act'&nbsp;– seriously|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/music_blog/2011/12/jennifer-lopez-named-worlds-greatest-musical-comeback-act-seriously.html|work=Los Angeles Times |accessdate=January 29, 2012|date=December 13, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Rodriguez|first1=Priscilla|title=7 Latino Celebrities With Guinness World Records|url=http://www.latina.com/entertainment/celebrity/latino-celebrities-stars-guinness-world-records#6|website=Latina |accessdate=December 5, 2015|date=September 19, 2014}}</ref> Lopez remains the only entertainer to have a number one album and film simultaneously in the United States.<ref>{{cite news |title=Billboard 200|work=Billboard|date=February 10, 2001|volume= 113| issue = 6|page=88|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ghMEAAAAMBAJ&q=Jennifer+Lopez+J.Lo#v=snippet&q=Jennifer%20Lopez%20J.Lo&f=false|accessdate=April 13, 2013}}</ref> In 2013, she was presented with the prestigious landmark 2,500th star on the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]] for her musical contributions, with the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' declaring, "It's hard to think of a more emblematic figure of multitasking modern celebrity".<ref>{{cite news|last=Johnson|first=Reed|title=Jennifer Lopez, new Walk of Famer, cites Fonda among role models|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/posts/la-et-ms-jennifer-lopez-gets-star-on-hollywood-walk-of-fame-20130623,0,4699689.story?track=rss&utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed%3A+PopHiss+%28Pop+%26+Hiss+Music+Blog%29|work=Los Angeles Times |accessdate=June 26, 2013|date=June 23, 2013}}</ref> Furthermore, Lopez was honored with the [[Billboard Icon Award]] in 2014 for her contributions to the music industry, making her the first female recipient of the award.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ramirez|first1=Erika|title=Jennifer Lopez Receives Icon Award, Performs 'First Love' at the 2014 Billboard Music Awards|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/bbma-2014/6092051/jennifer-lopez-icon-award-billboard-music-awards|work=Billboard |accessdate=December 6, 2015|date=May 18, 2014}}</ref>

Famed for her distinctive fashion and style, ''[[Us Weekly]]'' magazine named Lopez "Style Icon" of the 2000s decade.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jennifer Lopez: Us' Style Icon of the Decade|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-style/pictures/jlo-through-the-years-2010204/7767|work=[Us Weekly |accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref> The [[Green Versace dress of Jennifer Lopez|Green Versace "Jungle Dress"]] that she wore at the [[42nd Annual Grammy Awards]] in 2000 was voted the fifth most iconic dress of all time in a poll run by ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]''.<ref name="Telegraph08">{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/3167702/Liz-Hurley-safety-pin-dress-voted-the-greatest-dress.html|author=Urmee Khan|title=Liz Hurley 'safety pin' dress voted the greatest dress |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=October 9, 2008|accessdate=May 1, 2011|location=London}}</ref> The images of Lopez wearing the dress became the most popular search query of all time at that point, and subsequently led to the creation of [[Google Search|Google]]'s [[Image retrieval|image search]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Schmidt|first1=Eric |authorlink=Eric Schmidt |title=The Tinker's Apprentice|url=http://www.project-syndicate.org/commentary/google-european-commission-and-disruptive-technological-change-by-eric-schmidt-2015-01 |publisher=Project-syndicate.org|accessdate=January 25, 2015|date=January 19, 2015}}</ref> Her style has influenced a range of celebrities.<ref name="styleicons">{{cite web|url=http://photos.essence.com/galleries/kelly_rowland__style_icons#!881733|title=Kelly Rowland: Style Icons|work=Essence |accessdate=May 12, 2012}}</ref><ref name="kimj">{{cite web|last=Coughlan|first=Maggie|title=Kim Kardashian Considers Jennifer Lopez a Style Icon|url=http://www.popeater.com/2011/02/15/kim-kardashian-qvc-fashion-week/|publisher=PopEater|accessdate=January 10, 2012|date=February 15, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Harp|first=Justin|title=Jennifer Love Hewitt: 'Jennifer Lopez's style is amazing'|url=http://www.digitalspy.com.au/showbiz/news/a470919/jennifer-love-hewitt-jennifer-lopezs-style-is-amazing.html|publisher=Digital Spy |accessdate=April 9, 2013|date=April 6, 2013}}</ref> Her record-breaking fragrance line has become the most successful celebrity line in the world, with sales exceeding $2 billion.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/jennifer-lopez-and-nuvotv-announce-exclusive-creative-production-and-marketing-partnership-169416666.html |title=Jennifer Lopez and nuvoTV Announce Exclusive Creative, Production and Marketing Partnership |location=Los Angeles |date=September 12, 2012 |publisher=PRNewswire |accessdate=2014-07-20}}</ref> Lopez has been credited as an influence or inspiration by a range of entertainers, including [[Jessica Alba]],<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tewari|first1=Nidhi|title=Jessica Alba Talks About Her Entrepreneurial Side, Says She Considers Jennifer Lopez As Her Idol|url=http://www.ibtimes.com.au/jessica-alba-talks-about-her-entrepreneurial-side-says-she-considers-jennifer-lopez-her-idol-1370954|website=[[International Business Times]]|accessdate=September 19, 2014|date=September 18, 2014}}</ref> [[Adrienne Bailon]],<ref name="Latina 2013" /> [[Kat DeLuna]],<ref name="DeLuna">{{cite news|title=J.Lo's new song sounds suspiciously like one from Hispanic hottie Kat DeLuna|url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2011-01-19/gossip/27087962_1_jlo-kat-deluna-similarities|work=New York Daily News |accessdate=February 4, 2012|date=January 19, 2011}}</ref> [[Mike Doughty]],<ref name="dep13">{{cite web|last=Letkemman|first=Jessica|title=Mike Doughty Opens 'Book of Drugs,' Says J.Lo & Music Thieves Saved His Life|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/464820/mike-doughty-opens-book-of-drugs-says-jlo-music-thieves-saved-his-life|work=Billboard |accessdate=February 26, 2012|location=New York|date=December 7, 2011}}</ref> [[Becky G]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/becky-g-talks-working-with-jennifer-lopez-i-still-get-goosebumps-when-i-watch-the-video_article_78034 |title=Becky G Talks Working With Jennifer Lopez: 'I Still Get Goosebumps When I Watch The Video' |publisher=Accesshollywood.com |date=April 14, 2013 |accessdate=April 19, 2013}}</ref> [[Selena Gomez]],<ref name=SelenaGomez>{{cite news| url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2012/06/08/selena-gomez-gets-racy-in-elle-photoshoot/ | publisher=Fox News Latino | title=Selena Gomez Gets Racy in 'Elle' Photoshoot | date=June 8, 2012}}</ref> [[Kelly Key]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universomusical.com.br/materia.asp?mt=sim&id=170&cod=po|title=Kelly Key busca o sucesso de Christina Aguilera, Jennifer Lopez, Britney Spears, Madonna e Janet Jackson|work=Universo Musical|accessdate=January 7, 2012}}</ref> [[Q'orianka Kilcher]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crushable.com/2008/09/19/entertainment/flashback-qorianka-kilcher-thanks-j-lo-at-the-alma-awards/ |title=Flashback: Q'orianka Kilcher Thanks J-Lo at the Alma Awards |publisher=Crushable |date=September 19, 2008 |accessdate=April 19, 2013}}</ref> [[Beyoncé]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Castro|first=Peter|title=Beyoncé's Latin Soul|url=http://www.peopleenespanol.com/article/beyonces-latin-soul|work=[[People en Español]] |accessdate=July 4, 2013}}</ref> [[Demi Lovato]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Demi Lovato inspired by Jennifer Lopez|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/music/demi-lovato-inspired-by-jennifer-lopez/|website=[[The Indian Express]] |accessdate=September 21, 2015|date=March 6, 2015}}</ref> [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Kit|first=Zorianna|title=Pitbull on music, Jennifer Lopez and 'Epic'|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/pitbull-on-music-jennifer-lopez-and-epic/2013/05/23/bc108dbc-c314-11e2-914f-a7aba60512a7_story.html|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=May 26, 2013|date=May 26, 2013}}</ref> [[Francia Raisa]],<ref name="Latina 2013">{{cite web|last1=Rodriguez|first1=Priscilla|title=10 Stars J.Lo Influenced|url=http://www.latina.com/entertainment/stars-celebrities-jennifer-lopez-influenced|website=[[Latina (magazine)|Latina]] |accessdate=December 8, 2015|date=August 31, 2013}}</ref> [[Naya Rivera]],<ref>{{cite news |last=Cosgrove |first=Sheila |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20731121,00.html |title=Naya Rivera Hopes to Follow in Jennifer Lopez's Footsteps – Glee, Jennifer Lopez, Naya Rivera |work=People |accessdate=2014-07-20}}</ref> [[Stooshe]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com.au/music/news/a502912/j-lo-trains-in-hair-and-make-up-for-an-hour-before-shows-say-stooshe.html |title=J-Lo trains in hair and make-up for an hour before shows, say Stooshe |publisher=Digital Spy |date=August 1, 2013 |accessdate=August 10, 2013}}</ref> [[Fifth Harmony]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teennick.com/blog/teennick-top-10-an-interview-with-fifth-harmony.html |title=TeenNick Top 10: An Interview With Fifth Harmony |work=[[Teen Nick]] |date=August 22, 2013 |accessdate=March 28, 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130822150229/http://www.teennick.com/blog/teennick-top-10-an-interview-with-fifth-harmony.html |archivedate=August 22, 2013 }}</ref> and [[Kerry Washington]].<ref name="KW1">{{cite news |title=Kerry Washington: Lopez inspired me|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/news/kerry-washington-lopez-inspired-me-16111987.html|newspaper=The Belfast Telegraph |accessdate=February 4, 2012|date=February 1, 2012}}</ref>

In 2014, scientists named a species of aquatic [[mite]] found in Puerto Rico, ''[[Litarachna lopezae]]'', after Lopez.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.theguardian.com/music/2014/jul/17/scientists-name-new-species-of-water-mite-after-jennifer-lopez |title=Scientists name new species of water mite after Jennifer Lopez |author=Harriet Gibsone |date=17 July 2014 |website=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=19 July 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/celebrity/ls-celebrity-news/puerto-rican-water-mite-named-after-jennifer-lopez-20140717-ztu05.html |title=Puerto Rican water mite named after Jennifer Lopez |author=Danica Coto |date=17 July 2014 |website=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |accessdate=19 July 2014 }}</ref>
